description: This file is a header (.h) file that declares external API functions related to a TFTP client object within the ANSC framework. It contains function prototypes for creating, removing, enrolling, and initializing TFTP client objects, as well as the licensing and copyright information.

methods.name: AnscCreateTftpClient
methods.description: Creates a new TFTP client object with specified container, owner, and reserved contexts.

methods.name: AnscTftpcoCreate
methods.description: Allocates and initializes a new TFTP client object.

methods.name: AnscTftpcoRemove
methods.description: Removes and deallocates the specified TFTP client object.

methods.name: AnscTftpcoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects or components into the TFTP client object.
